<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 29 at 8:31PM CDT  by NWS Huntsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Lauderdale, northwestern Limestone, northeastern Colbert and north
central Lawrence Counties through 915 PM CDT...
At 830 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Rogersville, or 13 miles northwest of Athens. This
storm was drifting slowly northwest.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Athens, Rogersville, Lexington, Anderson, Lester, Good Springs,
Cartwright, Coxey, Oliver and Mt Rozell.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
